      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "this",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") He brings a more severe charge against the rulers, than in ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 3:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " against the people.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁ λίθος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the stone",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The article refers the hearers back to prophecy. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 21:42",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", note.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὑφʼ ὑμῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "by you",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") This is added with boldness of speech.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰς κεφαλὴν γωνίας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the head of the corner",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") This is explained in the following verse. The very rejection on the part of the builders proves the stone [to be the one chosen of God].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 11.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "- He",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "this",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the builders",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "builders",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "was made",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "is become",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V. He is the stone. He had just appealed to their own senses; he now adds the witness of their own prophets. These had declared that the stone which was set at naught by the builders should become the chief corner-stone; just as it had come to pass. The quotation is from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 118:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; only St. Luke here substitutes the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐξουθενεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", to set at naught, for that used by the LXX., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀποδοκιμάζειν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "to",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " refuse, or reject as unfit. The word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐξουθενεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is applied directly to our Saviour in ",
        "children": []
      },
